## Important note

I assumed that this part:

```ts
if (currency !== debitAccountCurrency)
```

means:

```ts
this.fileImport?.fileCurrencyCode !== item.sourceAccountNumber currency
```

because your validation request already uses:

```ts
currencyCode: this.fileImport?.fileCurrencyCode!
```

If the currency should instead come from each `FileImportContent` row, replace this line:

```ts
const fileCurrencyCode = this.normalizeCurrencyCode(
  this.fileImport?.fileCurrencyCode
);
```

with something like:

```ts
const fileCurrencyCode = this.normalizeCurrencyCode(item.currencyCode);
```

depending on your actual model property name.
